@startuml seq_07_follow_unfollow_user
title Sequence Diagram: UC-07 Follow / Unfollow User

actor User
participant "User Web" as Frontend
participant "Follow Controller" as Controller
participant "Follow Service" as Service
participant "User Repository" as Repo

User -> Frontend: (1.1) Open another user's profile
User -> Frontend: (2.1) Click Follow / Unfollow button
Frontend -> Controller: (2.2) POST /api/users/{target_id}/follow (or DELETE)
Controller -> Service: (3.1) Validate authenticated user and target user
Service -> Repo: (3.2) Check target user exists
Repo --> Service: (3.3) User exists

alt Action is Follow
    Service -> Repo: (4.1) Create follow relationship
    Repo --> Service: (4.2) Relationship created
    Service -> Repo: (5.1) Increase follower/feed visibility state
else Action is Unfollow
    Service -> Repo: (6.1) Remove follow relationship
    Repo --> Service: (6.2) Relationship removed
    Service -> Repo: (7.1) Reduce follower/feed visibility state
end

Service --> Controller: (8.1) Updated follow status
Controller --> Frontend: (8.2) 200 OK
Frontend --> User: (8.3) Update UI button state
@enduml
